20 "3-15-411. Term of service of jurors. (1) The persons whose names are so returned are known as
21 regular jurors and noticed must serve for 1 year and until other persons are selected and returned unless they
22 are excused by the court or a judge pursuant to 3-15-501.
23 (2) If Except as provided in subsection (3), if jurors are drawn before the selection and return of the
24 new jury list as provided in this part and thereafter a new jury list is subsequently returned, they shall continue
25 to serve as jurors, if the business of the court requires the attendance of a jury, for a period not exceeding 90
26 days.
